al society in the Cerdanya, a valley in the eastern Pyrenees divided between Spain and France in 1659. This study shuttles between two levels, between the center and the periphery. It connects the ";macroscopic"; political and diplomatic history of France and Spain, from the Old Regime monarchies to the national territorial states of the later nineteenth century; and the ";molecular"; history--the historical ethnography--of Catalan village communities, rural nobles, and peasants in the borderland. On the frontier, these two histories come together, and they can be told as one.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aSelf-determination, NationalzCerdaña (Spain and France)xHistory. 0aSelf-determination, NationalzCerdaña (Spain and France)xHistory. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh  a17th century european history.  a18th century european history.  a19th century european history.  aborderland.  aboundary.  acatalan.  acerdanya.  acounter identity.  adelimitation.  adiplomatic history.  aethnography.  aeurope.  afrance.  afrench history.  afrench revolution.  aidentity.  amonarchy.  anation building.  anational boundary.  aold regime.  apolitical history.  aproperty.  apyrenees.  aresistance.  arural nobles.  arural.  aspain.  aspanish history.  astate building.  aterritory.  atreaties of bayonne.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052007415640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520911215?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520911215423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520911215/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-all